The following issues were recently filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission: 

Loews Corp., proposed offering of $600 million of liquid yield option notes, via Merrill Lynch Capital Markets. 

MFS Special Value Trust, initial offering of 10 million common shares, via Kidder, Peabody & Co., Smith Barney, Harris Upham & Co., and Wheat First Butcher & Singer Capital Markets. 

Old Spaghetti Warehouse, Inc., offering of 560,000 common shares, via Epplers, Guerin & Turner Inc. 

Potomac Electric Power Co., proposed offering of 2.2 million common shares, via Merrill Lynch, Pierce and Fenner & Smith Inc. 

Tyco Toys Inc., proposed offering of $50 million convertible debentures, via Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. 

VISX Inc., proposed offering of 707,997 common shares, via holders. 

